As of early 2026, 3.06 is the definitive stable version for your hardware. It was a significant update because it introduced the Framework EC device and fixed the OPAL drive bug (where some SSDs would just disappear on reboot).

The next major update for your generation is expected to focus on fine-tuning the NPU (Neural Processing Unit) and further power efficiency tweaks, but Framework is quite conservative with BIOS releases—if they haven't pushed it to testing yet, it's not ready for daily use.

