Since you're on Hyprland, you likely don't have a "Software Center" sending you notifications. You’ll need a few lightweight tools to keep an eye on things.

1. Firmware & System Notifications
Since you have the fwupd-refresh.timer running, the easiest way to get notified is to use swaync (Sway Notification Center) or mako. These are the standard notification daemons for Hyprland.

Install a daemon: sudo pacman -S swaync (recommended for its built-in control center).

Update check: Add a line to your waybar config or a simple cron script that runs fwupdmgr get-updates and pipes the output to notify-send if updates are found.

2. Battery Health & Wear (The "Framework way")
Framework laptops use the ChromeOS EC, which stores battery health data. You can read this directly from the kernel's power supply interface.

Quick Command:

Bash
cat /sys/class/power_supply/BAT1/capacity_level    # Should say "Normal"
cat /sys/class/power_supply/BAT1/energy_full      # Current full charge capacity
cat /sys/class/power_supply/BAT1/energy_full_design # Original design capacity
