Pro Tip: For the Intel Ultra 7, you should also install power-profiles-daemon or tlp. Many Hyprland users prefer power-profiles-daemon because it integrates nicely with Waybar to switch between "Power Saver," "Balanced," and "Performance."

3. SSD Health Check
Since you have a WD BLACK SN850X (an absolute beast of a drive), you want to monitor its "Percentage Used" and "Critical Warnings."

Install the tool:

Bash
sudo pacman -S smartmontools
Run the check:

Bash
sudo smartctl -a /dev/nvme0n1
What to look for:

Percentage Used: This is the % of the rated TBW (Total Bytes Written) you've used. If it's under 5%, your drive is basically brand new.

Data Units Written: Shows how much total data has been moved.

Media and Data Integrity Errors: This must be 0. If it’s not, back up your data immediately.

🔋 A Quick Framework Battery Tip
Since you're on Arch, you can set a Charge Limit to stop the battery at 80% if you're usually plugged in. This is the single best thing you can do for Framework battery longevity.

The Command:

Bash
echo 80 | sudo tee /sys/class/power_supply/BAT1/charge_control_end_threshold
(Note: This resets on reboot unless you add it to a udev rule or use a tool like ectool).

